This note addresses remaining correctness issues in the Freelinks plugin following #9084 and #9397.

Fixes:
* Incorrect State Transition: The Aho-Corasick search loop contained a duplicated root-node check that could cause a character to be processed twice, producing false matches. Replaced with the standard single transition pattern.
* Incomplete Output Collection: A hard limit of 10 on failure-link traversal could silently drop valid matches. The root node's outputs were also skipped by an early break. Replaced with a complete failure-chain walk.
* Longest-Match Not Honoured: A shorter title match could occupy positions needed by a longer overlapping title, causing the longer match to be incorrectly rejected (e.g. "雪狼" blocking "雪狼湖"). Replaced position-marking with greedy left-to-right selection, always preferring the longest match at each position.
* Dead Code in getStats(): A local patternCount variable was computed but never returned; this.patternCount was returned instead. Removed the unused variable.
* CJK Word Boundary Intent: CJK titles were passing word boundary checks by accident rather than by design. Added an explicit early return for CJK matches, reflecting that CJK scripts have no word boundary concept.

Impact:
* More reliable longest-match linking for multilingual wikis, particularly for Chinese titles containing shared substrings.
* Eliminated a class of false matches caused by incorrect Aho-Corasick traversal.
